text: Bunschoten is a municipality in the province Utrecht, the Netherlands. Bunschoten is also called Bunschoten-spakenburg because the two villages Bunschoten and Spakenburg “grew” into each other. Bunschoten was in the early ages a farmers village and Spakenburg a fishers village. Category:Settlements in Utrecht (province) Category:Municipalities of Utrecht (province)
title: Bunschoten
